# StoryCall Corporate Site

## Project Overview

Corporate marketing website for StoryCall (storycall.org). Converts
messages from SMS, Instagram, and other apps into scheduled phone
calls for people who don't use social media.

Static single-page HTML website with no build process, dependencies,
or backend. Hosted via GitHub Pages with custom domain.


## Architecture

- single_file_architecture: Everything (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) is in
                             `index.html`
- no_build_process         : Served directly as-is
- deployment               : GitHub Pages (configured via CNAME file)
- main_app                 : Separate application at app.storycall.org
                             (not in this repo)


## File Structure

- `index.html` - Complete website with inline CSS and JavaScript
- `CNAME`      - Custom domain configuration for GitHub Pages
- `README.md`  - Basic project description


## Sections in index.html

- Header with navigation (sticky)
- Hero/main content area with CTA buttons
- `#how`   - How it works (3-step process)
- `#help`  - Help/contact form (mailto-based)
- `#faq`   - Expandable FAQ items using `<details>`
- `#legal` - Full Privacy Policy and Terms & Conditions (expandable)
- `#about` - Company background
- Footer


## Key Design Patterns

- styling_approach: All CSS is inline in `<style>` tag with CSS
                    custom properties, responsive media queries,
                    subtle surface overlays, minimal color palette.
- no_backend      : Contact form uses `mailto:` action.
- java_script     : Minimal vanilla JS for dynamic copyright year
                    and effective dates for Privacy/Terms.


## Making Changes

- Maintain inline architecture (don't extract CSS/JS)
- Preserve accessibility attributes (aria-label, etc.)
- Keep design system using CSS custom properties in `:root`
- Test responsive breakpoints (`breakpoint_*` vars; literals in
  `@media/@container`)


## Deployment

Changes to `main` are auto-deployed to storycall.org via GitHub
Pages. No build or deployment commands needed.

Support email: help@storycall.org
